byline.contributor: Alison Smale reported from Vienna, Melissa Eddy from Berlin, and Kareem Fahim from Cairo. Reporting was contributed by Palko Karasz from London, Nick Cumming-Bruce from Geneva, David D. Kirkpatrick and Merna Thomas from Cairo, and Rick Gladstone from New York.
byline.original: By ALISON SMALE, MELISSA EDDY and KAREEM FAHIM

abstract: Authorities arrest at least four people in connection with refrigeration truck abandoned in Austria containing remains of 71 people in rear hold who apparently died of asphyxiation; incident is part of humanitarian crisis brought on by African and Middle Eastern political instability that causes thousands to flee to Europe in overloaded and unsafe transport.
lead_paragraph: Deaths of about 150 people at sea near Libya and 71 found in a truck in Austria came as the United Nations reported a surge in 2015 migrations.

headline.main: Europe Reels From More Migrant Deaths on Land and Sea
headline.print_headline: More Migrants Die at Sea as Austria Toll Surpasses Initial Estimates
